request.description: This endpoint makes an HTTP GET request to retrieve exam information based on the provided college, specialty, and exam UUIDs. The request should include the query parameters college_uuid, specialty_uuid, and exam_uuid. The response will be in JSON format with a status code of 200. The response body will contain an array of exam data, including question text and answers. The status field indicates the success of the request, and the message field may contain additional information. The statusCode field provides additional status information, and the college_uuid field may also be included in the response.

### Calculate User Exam

This endpoint allows the user to calculate the exam score.

#### Request Body

- `data` (array of objects)
    - `question_text` (string, optional): The text of the question.
    - `answers` (array of objects)
        - `answer_text` (string, optional): The text of the answer.
        - `status` (boolean): The status of the answer.
        - `choose` (boolean): The chosen answer.

#### Query Parameters

- `college_uuid` (string): The UUID of the college.
    

#### Response

- `data` (object)
    - `questions` (array of objects)
        - `question_text` (string, optional): The text of the question.
        - `answers` (array of objects)
            - `answer_text` (string, optional): The text of the answer.
            - `status` (boolean): The status of the answer.
            - `choose` (boolean): The chosen answer.
    - `mark` (integer): The calculated exam score.
- `status` (boolean): The status of the response.
- `message` (string, optional): Any additional message.
- `statusCode` (integer): The status code of the response.
- `college_uuid` (string): The UUID of the college.
